Interestingly, this is a duplicate of https://bugzilla.gnome.org/show_bug.cgi?id=750365. Back then I've send a patch to the mailing list, but apparently my mail never made it through.

````diff
 uri.c | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/uri.c b/uri.c
index 2bd5720..9c7ca05 100644
--- a/uri.c
+++ b/uri.c
@@ -1212,11 +1212,13 @@ xmlSaveUri(xmlURIPtr uri) {
 		 ((p[1] >= 'A') && (p[1] <= 'Z'))) &&
 		(p[2] == ':') &&
 	        (xmlStrEqual(BAD_CAST uri->scheme, BAD_CAST "file"))) {
-		if (len + 3 >= max) {
+		if (len + 5 >= max) {
                     temp = xmlSaveUriRealloc(ret, &max);
                     if (temp == NULL) goto mem_error;
                     ret = temp;
 		}
+		ret[len++] = '/';
+		ret[len++] = '/';
 		ret[len++] = *p++;
 		ret[len++] = *p++;
 		ret[len++] = *p++;
````

That patch would no longer apply, but the idea was to report `C:///does_not_exist.xml`.

Anyhow, I'll try with 2.13.4 (still using 2.11.9), and report back.
